callLoggingNumServers.name: callLoggingNumServers
callLoggingNumServers.description: The maximum number of Call Logging servers supported by the system.

callLoggingServerTable.name: callLoggingServerTable
callLoggingServerTable.description: A list of entries for Call Logging Server addresses.

callLoggingServerEntry.name: callLoggingServerEntry
callLoggingServerEntry.description: Entry holding information about the currently active Call Logging Server and the address of a Server.

callLoggingServerIndex.name: callLoggingServerIndex
callLoggingServerIndex.description: The index number for this Call Logging server entry. Its value ranges from 1 to 'callLoggingNumServers'. and identifies which server entry is associated with.

callLoggingCurrentServerFlag.name: callLoggingCurrentServerFlag
callLoggingCurrentServerFlag.description: Value indicates whether this entry is the current Call Logging server or not.

callLoggingServerIPAddress.name: callLoggingServerIPAddress
callLoggingServerIPAddress.description: The IP address of Call Logging server. The value 0.0.0.0 is returned if entry is invalid.

callLoggingEnableActiveServer.name: callLoggingEnableActiveServer
callLoggingEnableActiveServer.description: This is used to set the active call Logging server. If set to enable(2) it will enable the call Logging server, A read on the variable will return notApplicable(1).

callLoggingStatus.name: callLoggingStatus
callLoggingStatus.description: Enable/Disable call loggin support. Note: Prior to enable the call Logging, one of the Call Logging server must be setup with a valid IP address. If the server IP address is not setup, a SET to this object will return with a bad value error.

callLoggingPortNumber.name: callLoggingPortNumber
callLoggingPortNumber.description: The UDP server port to use for Call Logging packets.

callLoggingKey.name: callLoggingKey
callLoggingKey.description: The (RADIUS_ACCT) call logging key to access server.

callLoggingTimeout.name: callLoggingTimeout
callLoggingTimeout.description: Number of seconds to wait for a response to previous Call Logging request sent to server.

callLoggingIdBase.name: callLoggingIdBase
callLoggingIdBase.description: The Base to use in reporting Call Logging ID.

callLoggingResetTime.name: callLoggingResetTime
callLoggingResetTime.description: The time to reset to the primary server after it has failed.

callLoggingStopPacketsOnly.name: callLoggingStopPacketsOnly
callLoggingStopPacketsOnly.description: Send call log Stop packets that have username=0. These are caused by connections that are dropped before authentication is done.

callLoggingRetryLimit.name: callLoggingRetryLimit
callLoggingRetryLimit.description: Number of retries before removing Call Logging packet. 0 means leave on retry list until maximum retry entries are exceeded.

callLoggingAssStatus.name: callLoggingAssStatus
callLoggingAssStatus.description: Indicates the status of Active Session Snapshot protocol. Writing the attribute with a nonzero value causes the start of an Active Session Snapshot. If no server is configured the Active Session Snapshot will abort immediatly, an active session can not be aborted

callLoggingDroppedPacketCount.name: callLoggingDroppedPacketCount
callLoggingDroppedPacketCount.description: Number of dropped Call Logging packets since the last Active Session Snapshot

callLoggingRadCompatMode.name: callLoggingRadCompatMode
callLoggingRadCompatMode.description: Indicates call logging RADIUS compatibility mode. This variable is deprecated, starting with TAOS Release 8.0. this variable has a fixed value of radVendorSpecific(4)
